"{\"abstract\":\"While the vast majority of existing work on automated essay scoring has focused on holistic scoring, researchers have recently begun work on scoring specific dimensions of essay quality. Nevertheless, progress on dimension-specific essay scoring is limited in part by the lack of annotated corpora. To facilitate advances in this area, we design a scoring rubric for scoring a core, yet unexplored dimension of persuasive essay quality, thesis strength, and annotate a corpus of essays with thesis strength scores. We additionally identify the attributes that could impact thesis strength and annotate the essays with the values of these attributes, which, when predicted by computational models, could provide further feedback to students on why her essay receives a particular thesis strength score.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"9623089\",\"name\":\"Zixuan Ke\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/9623089\"},{\"authorId\":\"151349260\",\"name\":\"Hrishikesh Inamdar\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/151349260\"},{\"authorId\":\"144335190\",\"name\":\"H. Lin\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144335190\"},{\"authorId\":\"145106110\",\"name\":\"Vincent Ng\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145106110\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"2010.02660\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"39947629\",\"name\":\"Yohan Jo\"},{\"authorId\":\"3160363\",\"name\":\"Seo-Jin Bang\"},{\"authorId\":\"3364789\",\"name\":\"Emaad Manzoor\"},{\"authorId\":\"144547315\",\"name\":\"E. Hovy\"},{\"authorId\":\"1382576368\",\"name\":\"C. Reed\"}],\"doi\":\"10.18653/v1/2020.emnlp-main.1\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"33e5e4b079535957d1275497f8870ea57762a03d\",\"title\":\"Detecting Attackable Sentences in Arguments\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/33e5e4b079535957d1275497f8870ea57762a03d\",\"venue\":\"EMNLP\",\"year\":2020},{\"arxivId\":null,\"